00:00:00.599 --> 00:00:05.080
First, you must spread a thick layer of peanut
butter onto the white part of a slice of bread.

00:00:05.080 --> 00:00:08.651
You can only spread the peanut butter on the
white part, and the white part only.

00:00:08.651 --> 00:00:12.340
You may only spread peanut butter on one side.

00:00:12.340 --> 00:00:15.810
Spreading peanut butter on both sides will
provide an inferior sandwich.

00:00:15.810 --> 00:00:19.480
Next, you must spread a thick layer of jelly
onto the white part of a slice of bread.

00:00:19.480 --> 00:00:22.950
You can only spread the jelly on the white
part, and the white part only.

00:00:22.950 --> 00:00:25.900
You may only spread jelly on one side.

00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:29.030
Spreading jelly on both sides will provide
an inferior sandwich.

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:33.230
You cannot spread jelly onto the same slice
of bread onto which you have spread peanut

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:34.230
butter.

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:37.829
Also, you cannot spread peanut butter or jelly
onto more than one slice of bread, as this

00:00:37.829 --> 00:00:41.030
will provide an undesired excess of either
ingredient.

00:00:41.030 --> 00:00:45.319
Additionally, only peanut butter and jelly
can be spread onto these slices of bread;

00:00:45.319 --> 00:00:50.679
no other ingredient will suffice, and no substitute
can be used in a sandwich that is to be legitimately

00:00:50.679 --> 00:00:53.760
recognized as a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.

00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:58.410
Likewise, only bread may be the substance
upon which the peanut butter and jelly are

00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:02.530
spread, as anything else does not fit the
standards of a peanut butter and jelly sandwich;

00:01:02.530 --> 00:01:06.740
if the peanut butter and jelly are spread
onto a culinary medium that isn't bread, the

00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:10.030
meal at hand simply is not a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

00:01:10.030 --> 00:01:13.460
Once you have accomplished spreading a thin
layer of peanut butter onto the white of one

00:01:13.460 --> 00:01:17.950
side of one slice of bread, and likewise has
been accomplished using grape jelly on a separate

00:01:17.950 --> 00:01:22.680
slice of bread, you must match the slices
of bread up to each other, forming a peanut

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:24.420
butter and jelly sandwich.

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:28.260
In this scenario, the peanut butter-covered
face of bread must be facing the jelly-covered

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:32.530
face of the second slice of bread so that
the peanut butter surface touched the surface

00:01:32.530 --> 00:01:33.740
of the jelly.

00:01:33.740 --> 00:01:38.090
The surface of the peanut butter is not allowed
to touch a jelly-less substance of bread,

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:41.799
resulting in the jelly facing outwards, and
likewise applies to the jelly.

00:01:41.799 --> 00:01:46.670
If a substance is found facing on the outside
of the sandwich, the product will not be accepted

00:01:46.670 --> 00:01:48.740
as a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.

00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:52.619
The side with peanut butter and the side with
jelly on it must match up and stick together

00:01:52.619 --> 00:01:54.610
to form one solid sandwich.

00:01:54.610 --> 00:01:58.710
When the eater picks up the sandwich, he or
she must hold both pieces of bread at the

00:01:58.710 --> 00:02:03.950
same time, or else one slice will fall off,
and eating only one slice of bread will not

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:08.880
be recognized as the same or even similar
to eating a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.

00:02:08.880 --> 00:02:11.500
Next, you must take a bite of the sandwich.

00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:15.680
This action will consist of moving the sandwich
within such a close proximity of your face

00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:20.220
that a small "bite" of the sandwich will enter
your mouth for you to mash up with your teeth.

00:02:20.220 --> 00:02:25.130
This bite must be a bite that includes both
slices of bread, peanut butter and jelly.

00:02:25.130 --> 00:02:29.740
Make sure that all obstructions are clear
from the mouth and esophagus, not including

00:02:29.740 --> 00:02:34.120
